Action has been initiated against owners of 11 petrol/diesel retail outlets in the district for failing to comply with rules under the Legal Metrology Act, 2009.According to a release, a team of officials, including the Legal Metrology Departmentâ€™s Deputy Controller, Vellore, conducted checks at 102 outlets in December last. They found sale of less quantity of fuel at 11 petrol/diesel retail outlets.Following this, action was initiated against owners of these outlets under the Legal Metrology Act 2009.